# --- Write initial triage report ---------------------------------------------

initial_triage() {
    info "Building initial_triage report"
    local path="${1:?initial_triage requires an output path}"

    # -------------------------------------------------------------------------
    # region T1. Resolve report values
    # -------------------------------------------------------------------------

    case_id="${INPUT[CASE]:-Unknown Case-ID}"
    title="${INPUT[TITLE]:-Untitled investigation}"
    description="${INPUT[DESCRIPTION]:-No description provided}"
    severity="${INPUT[SEVERITY]:-Unclassified}"
    asset="${INPUT[ASSET]:-Asset Unknown}"
    site="${INPUT[SITE]:-Unknown}"
    case_status="${INPUT[STATUS]:-Open — pending initial triage}"
    profile="${INPUT[PROFILE]:-default}"

    reported_by="${INPUT[REPORTED_BY]:-Unknown}"
    owner="${INPUT[OWNER]:-Unassigned}"
    first_observed="${INPUT[FIRST_OBSERVED]:-Unknown}"
    last_observed="${INPUT[LAST_OBSERVED]:-Unknown}"
    operational_impact="${INPUT[OPERATIONAL_IMPACT]:-Not yet assessed}"
    reproduction_status="${INPUT[REPRO_STATUS]:-Not attempted}"
    containment_status="${INPUT[CONTAINMENT_STATUS]:-Not yet documented}"
    affected_scope="${INPUT[AFFECTED_SCOPE]:-Unknown}"
    recent_change="${INPUT[RECENT_CHANGE]:-None identified}"
    confidence="${INPUT[TRIAGE_CONFIDENCE]:-Low — initial information only}"
    generated_utc="$(timestamp)"

    # -------------------------------------------------------------------------
    # endregion T1. Resolve report values
    # -------------------------------------------------------------------------

    # -------------------------------------------------------------------------
    # region T2. Log/debug resolved values
    # -------------------------------------------------------------------------

    debug "Case-ID: $case_id"
    debug "Case Title: $title"
    debug "Case Description: $description"
    debug "Case Severity: $severity"
    debug "Asset(s) Affected: $asset"
    debug "Site(s) affected: $site"
    debug "Case status: $case_status"
    debug "Capture profile: $profile"
    debug "Reporter: $reported_by"
    debug "Issue owner: $owner"
    debug "First observed: $first_observed"
    debug "Last observed: $last_observed"
    debug "Operational impact: $operational_impact"
    debug "Reproduction status: $reproduction_status"
    debug "Containment status: $containment_status"
    debug "Affected scope: $affected_scope"
    debug "Recent change: $recent_change"
    debug "Confidence: $confidence"
    debug "Report generated at: $generated_utc"

    # -------------------------------------------------------------------------
    # endregion T2. Log resolved values
    # -------------------------------------------------------------------------

    # -------------------------------------------------------------------------
    # region T3. Write initial triage report
    # -------------------------------------------------------------------------

    write_file_stream "$path" <<-INITIAL_TRIAGE
	# ${case_id} — ${title}

	> **Initial-triage snapshot:** This document records what is currently known,
	> unknown, assumed, and planned. It is not a final root-cause determination.

	## 1. Case control

	- **Case ID:** \`${case_id}\`
	- **Description:** ${description}
	- **Severity:** ${severity}
	- **Status:** ${case_status}
	- **Asset:** \`${asset}\`
	- **Site:** \`${site}\`
	- **Reported by:** ${reported_by}
	- **Investigation owner:** ${owner}
	- **Collection profile:** \`${profile}\`
	- **Report generated:** ${generated_utc}
	- **Triage confidence:** ${confidence}

	## 2. Executive summary

	### Expected behavior

	- TODO: State what the system, vehicle, subsystem, or operator expected to happen.

	### Observed behavior

	- TODO: State what was directly observed without interpretation.
	- TODO: Include the relevant time window and operating phase.
	- TODO: Describe whether the behavior was transient, persistent, or intermittent.

	### Why it matters

	- **Operational impact:** ${operational_impact}
	- TODO: State the immediate consequence or credible risk.
	- TODO: Distinguish actual impact from potential impact.

	### Current disposition

	- **Operational status:** ${case_status}
	- **Containment status:** ${containment_status}
	- TODO: State whether the asset may continue operating, is restricted, or is grounded.

	## 3. Safety and containment

	### Immediate safety assessment

	- [ ] No personnel-safety impact identified.
	- [ ] No public-safety impact identified.
	- [ ] No loss-of-control or flyaway concern identified.
	- [ ] No battery, thermal, fire, or electrical hazard identified.
	- [ ] No evidence-preservation risk remains.
	- [ ] Safety owner has reviewed the current disposition.

	### Containment already performed

	- TODO: Grounded, isolated, disabled, rolled back, restarted, swapped, or monitored.
	- TODO: Record who authorized the action and when.
	- TODO: Record whether containment altered or destroyed evidence.

	### Stop-work or escalation triggers

	- Reproduction involving unsafe vehicle behavior.
	- Evidence of expanding fleet or site scope.
	- Loss of trustworthy telemetry or event timing.
	- Recurrence after containment.
	- Any symptom inconsistent with the current severity classification.
	- TODO: Add mission-specific escalation triggers.

	## 4. Scope

	- **First observed:** ${first_observed}
	- **Last observed:** ${last_observed}
	- **Known affected scope:** ${affected_scope}
	- **Reproduction status:** ${reproduction_status}
	- **Recent relevant change:** ${recent_change}

	### Scope questions

	- [ ] One asset or multiple assets?
	- [ ] One site or multiple sites?
	- [ ] One software or firmware version?
	- [ ] One configuration or hardware revision?
	- [ ] One operator or operational procedure?
	- [ ] One environmental condition?
	- [ ] One flight or mission phase?
	- [ ] Similar symptoms found in earlier cases?

	## 5. Event timeline

